This feature allows to define the ordered hierarchical structure required for the XML Writer component to write the output XML file.

> Note

The data schema must contain a single **Root element**. Each Root element may contain one or more **elements**. In turn, elements may contain other cascading elements. All elements may be further characterized by **attributes**. For example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

The icon next to each structure component indicates its type:

**Icon**

**Type**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Document node **, set by default to the Root element

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Element**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Attribute**

> Tip

In order to generate the output file correctly, you need to define the following key nodes and attributes in the output structure that the XML Writer will produce; in particular:

- **Root **node, containing all the elements in the structure

- **Shipment **node, representing the smallest, indivisible item that can be shipped

**Shipment ID **attribute, as a child of the Shipment node

- **Document **node, identifying a single document layout

## Managing elements and attributes of the XML data schema
- Open the XML Writer's resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources.](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources)

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click ![](data:image/png;base64,)  to expand the context menu; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Adding an element to the structure
This feature allows to add an element at the same level as an existing element in the ordered hierarchical structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

- Select **Add element**. A new element is added to the structure; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Schema **tab, configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Name**

Name of the new element

**Dimension**

Maximum number of characters that the element can contain

**Type**

Select the element's type from the list. The available options are:

**builtin:string **(default) 

- **builtin:int **

- **builtin:date **

- **builtin:boolean **

- **builtin:binary**

> Important

In the DT3 UI, it is not possible to define custom types. To do so, switch to Classic Mode.

**Min occurrences**

Minimum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

When set to **0**, the attribute is optional.

To set the parameter as optional, you may also select the **Optional **checkbox.

**Max occurrences**

Maximum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

If there is no limit to the number of occurrences, select the **Unbounded **checkbox.

**Default value**

Default value to assign to the element

- Configure the required parameters in the **Settings **and **Values **tabs, as described in:

[DT3 XML Writer - Settings tab](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-xml-writer-settings-tab)

- [DT3 XML Writer - Values tab](/doxee-platform/docs/3-dt3-xml-writer-values-tab)

### Adding a child element to the structure
This feature allows to add a child element under an existing element in the ordered hierarchical structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

- Select **Add child element**. A new element is added to the structure, hierarchically nested under the selected element; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Schema **tab, configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Name**

Name of the new element

**Dimension**

Maximum number of characters that the element can contain

**Type**

Select the element's type from the list. The available options are:

**builtin:string **(default) 

- **builtin:int **

- **builtin:date **

- **builtin:boolean **

- **builtin:binary**

> Important

In the DT3 UI, it is not possible to define custom types. To do so, switch to Classic Mode.

**Min occurrences**

Minimum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

When set to **0**, the attribute is optional.

To set the parameter as optional, you may also select the **Optional **checkbox.

**Max occurrences**

Maximum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

If there is no limit to the number of occurrences, select the **Unbounded **checkbox.

**Default value**

Default value to assign to the element

- Configure the required parameters in the **Settings **and **Values **tabs, as described in:

[DT3 XML Writer - Settings tab](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-xml-writer-settings-tab)

- [DT3 XML Writer - Values tab](/doxee-platform/docs/3-dt3-xml-writer-values-tab)

### Adding an attribute to the structure
This feature allows to add an attribute to an element of the ordered hierarchical structure.

The functionality is useful, for example, when you want to define the properties or characteristics of an element of the structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

- Select **Add attribute**. A new attribute is added to the structure, hierarchically nested under the selected element; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Schema **tab, configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Node name**

Name of the new attribute

**Dimension**

Maximum number of characters that the attribute can contain

**Type**

Select the element's type from the list. The available options are:

**builtin:string **(default)

- **builtin:int**

- **builtin:date **

- **builtin:boolean**

- **builtin:binary**

**Mandatory**

Select this option to indicate that the attribute is mandatory.

**Default value**

Default value to assign to the attribute

- Configure the required parameters in the **Settings **and **Values **tabs, as described in:

[DT3 XML Writer - Settings tab](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-xml-writer-settings-tab)

- [DT3 XML Writer - Values tab](/doxee-platform/docs/3-dt3-xml-writer-values-tab)

### Selecting the Document node
This feature allows to select the Document node within the ordered hierarchical structure of the output schema.

The functionality is essential as it allows to indicate the document entity within the output file produced by the XML Writer.

> Note

The Document node identifies the single Document layout.

It is possible that, for a single shipment, more than one document (layout) is defined. Sometimes the term "template" is used as synonym of "document".

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

> Important

The Document node must be a repeatable child element of the Shipment node.

- Select **Set as Document node**. The selected element is now highlighted with the ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Selecting the Root node
This feature allows to select the node in the output structure that represent the Root of the data schema that the XML Writer component will produce.

> Note

The Root node contains all the elements in the structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

> Important

The Root node must be at the same level as the Document node, or higher.

- Select **Set as Root node**. The selected element is now highlighted with the ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Selecting the Shipment node
This feature allows to select the node in the output schema that represent the Shipment in the data schema that the XML Writer component will produce.

> Note

The Shipment node represent the smallest, indivisible item that can be shipped in the application; for example:

- For a paper mail delivery, the shipment represents the paper envelope.

- For an email delivery, the shipment represents the single delivered email.

For a paper mail delivery, the shipment represents the paper envelope. For an email delivery, the shipment represents the single delivered email.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

> Important

The Shipment node must be a repeatable child element of the Root node.

- Select **Set as Shipment node**. The selected element is now highlighted with the ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Selecting the Shipment ID
This feature allows to select the attribute in the output schema that represent the Shipment ID in the data schema that the XML Writer component will produce.

> Note

The Shipment ID attribute represents the unique ID of a Shipment.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

> Important

The Shipment ID attribute must be a direct child of the Shipment node.

- Select **Set as Shipment ID**. The selected element is now highlighted with the ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

> Important

This step is optional for the basic functioning of the writer, but mandatory to generate a Document Composition schema.
